[[File:Karjala.jpg|thumb|[[Karelian pasties]] topped with egg butter]]
'''Egg butter''' ({{Lang-fi|munavoi}}, {{Lang-et|munav<U+00F5>i}}) is a mixture of butter and chopped [[Boiled_egg#Hard-boiled_eggs|hard boiled egg]]s. Egg butter is one of the most popular innovations in [[Finnish cuisine]]. [[Karelian pasties]] are traditionally served with egg butter.<ref>Ojakangasm Beatrice A. (1999). [http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=y9z2sgGHWewC&q=%22Egg+butter%22#v=snippet&q=%22Egg%20butter%22&f=false ''The Great Scandinavian Baking Book''], pp. 269<U+2013>273. University of Minnesota Press. ISBN 0816634963</ref><ref>Symington, Andy and  Dunford, George (2009). [http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=SNatbAr2SFgC&pg=PA58 ''Finland''], p. 58. [[Lonely Planet]]. ISBN 1741047714</ref><ref>K<U+00E4>rne,  Karin Annus (2005). [http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=mPK75-OPQkQC&pg=PA=204 ''Estonian Tastes and Traditions''], p. 204. [[Hippocrene Books]]. ISBN 0781811228</ref>

